==English==

===Proverb===
'''[[The]] [[proof]] [[of]] [[the]] [[pudding]] [[is]] [[in]] [[the]] [[eating]]'''

# The only real test of something is as what it is intended to be used for.

Note that "proof" is used here in the sense of "test" (as in "proof-reading). The corruption of this proverb, "The proof is in the pudding", is hence incorrect and non-sense.

[[Category:Proverbs]]

[[pl:the proof of the pudding is in the eating]]